wikipedia_page.main: Sir Frederick Martin Williams, 2nd Baronet  (25 January 1830 – 3 September 1878) was a politician in the United Kingdom. He was Conservative Member of Parliament (MP) for Truro in Cornwall from 1865 until his death in 1878.
